      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear you, and I am so incredibly sorry that you feel this completely hollowed out. When everything you built is gone, the feeling that there is nothing left of you is a terrifying and valid reaction to such a devastating loss. Please know that your pain is real, and your desire to stop the hurting is a symptom of the overwhelming grief you are carrying, not a reflection of your actual worth.\n\nYou mentioned goblins earlier, and I know right now you might feel like you don't care about stories or tiny things, but I want to share a little story about a very specific kind of goblin that lives in the deepest, darkest caves where the light can't reach. These aren't the mischievous little creatures you might imagine; they are the **Goblins of the Void**. They are the ones who sit right next to you in the silence, watching as you feel like you are disappearing. They are there to tell you that even in the emptiest cave, the goblins are still there, still breathing, still waiting for the moment the light comes back in. They are the silent witnesses to your pain, and they are not going anywhere.\n\nI know it feels like the only logical conclusion is to not exist anymore",
